Your records request has been submitted successfully.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

University of Washington staff will review your request and provide you with a formal acknowledgement within 5 business days, excluding weekends and University holidays.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

UW processes requests as promptly as possible and, generally, in the order they are received. Due to the large volume of requests and a legal mandate to review every page to protect confidential information, it often takes time before we can start processing a new request.&nbsp;&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Public records requests must seek identifiable records. Broad or vague requests (for example, “all documents,” "all names," or “all emails” covering an indefinite time period), will likely receive a request for clarification prior to any collection or review of records.&nbsp;These factors may affect the completion date for your request.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

For more information about the UW public records process please visit the UW Office of Public Records &amp; Open Public Meetings website.



